{"name": "pybulk", "metadata": {"name": "pybulk", "version": "0.2.11", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/MrLpk/pybulk", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["PyMySQL", "SQLAlchemy"], "summary": "PyBulk is a Python module that to allow simple and fast bulk data insertion into databases", "upload_time": 1734063463}, "documentation": ["# PyBulk \ud83d\ude80\n[\u7b80\u4f53\u4e2d\u6587](README_CN.md) | English\n\nPyBulk is a Python module that wraps PyMySQL to allow simple and fast bulk data insertion into databases. With PyBulk, you can insert thousands of records into a database table in just a few lines of code.\n\nPyBulk builds on top of the PyMySQL library and connection pool to efficiently reuse connections and minimize latency. It handles all the low-level details of executing multiple INSERT statements while protecting your database from overload.\n\nSome of the main features of PyBulk include:\n* **Simple API**: Insert bulk data with just a few function calls. No complicated setup required.\n* **Speed**: Leverages PyMySQL's connection pool to quickly insert thousands of records.\n* **Reliability**: Includes error handling and recovery mechanisms to handle transient database errors. Retries failed queries automatically.\n* **Support for REPLACE INTO**: Upsert support allows you to replace existing records in a table or insert new ones.\n* **Compatibility**: Works with MySQL, MariaDB and AWS RDS. Compatible with Python 2 and 3.\n\nPyBulk allows you to focus on your application's logic rather than spending time building infrastructure to handle database load. It is a robust but lightweight solution ideal for batch data processing applications. \n## \ud83d\udcbe Installation\n\n```\npip install pybulk\n```\n\n## \ud83d\udd27 Usage:\n```\nimport pybulk\n\ncfg = {\n'host': 'localhost',\n'port':  3306,\n'user':  'root',\n'password': 'root',\n'db': 'info',\n'charset': 'utf8',\n}\n\ndb = pybulk.client(cfg)\n\nmy_data = [\n{'name': 'Peter', 'age': 21,},\n{'name': 'Harry', 'age': 35,},\n{'name': 'Mark', 'age': 40,},\n]\n\ndb.push_data('student', my_data, size=2000)\n\n# You can also run sql in pybulk like:\n\ndata = db.excute_sql('select * from school')\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pybulk", "documentation": ["Pybulk Library\n~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\n\nPybulk is a library help you to insert/update data to database more easiesly and more faster\n\nUsage:\n\nimport pybulk\n\ncfg = {\n    'host': 'localhost',\n    'port':  3306,\n    'user':  'root',\n    'password': 'root',\n    'db': 'info',\n    'charset': 'utf8',\n}\n\ndb = pybulk.client(cfg)\n\nmy_data = [\n    {'name': 'Peter', 'age': 21,},\n    {'name': 'Harry', 'age': 35,},\n    {'name': 'Mark', 'age': 40,},\n]\n\ndb.push_data('student', my_data, size=2000)\n\nYou can also run sql in pybulk like:\n\ndata = db.excute_sql('select * from school')"], "functions": [{"name": "pybulk.client", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cfg", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "alchemy", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "pybulk.DBInterface", "xref": {"fqname": "pybulk.dbinterface.DBInterface", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "pybulk.dbinterface", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "pybulk.dbinterface.CLS_NAME", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "pybulk.dbinterface.DBInterface", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "pybulk.dbinterface.DBInterface.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}